ideas. We cleared the bottom floor in about 5 hours, then we went up to the top floor. The pathing there sucks really really bad as most of you know, and it took about 30 minutes per mob to pull from Inny's chamber. After that we just decided to rush in and take stuff down one by one. It actually worked very well. <br>
    Zorlov picked out a lot of nice spots where he could pull without any pathing troubles. Instead of 1 mob per 30 mins, it was about 1 mob every 2-3 mins if that. Unfortunitly the raid took all day and once we started rolling on the second floor, everyone started passing out at the wheel. We had about 5 groups of six people and then we ended up with 3 full groups, and we were still taking them out pretty easily.<br>
    If the people that host the raid want to take out the second floor, they will have to skip almost all of the bottom floor and take mostly 52 plus people that already have the armor from the bottom floor. Our 57 enchanter had no luck with mezing the mobs, but with most of the pathing up there, they didn't have too worry about it because they couldn't fine their way of training us. At the end we went into a house and had about 6 mobs argo to us, but none of them found there way here, and we just took them 1 by one. This could be a plus if used right, and someways it can't be. <br>
<br>
Just Some information why i had time to write it, i'm bored =)<br>
